From: XR500v OpenWrt project
Subject: [PATCH] i2c: mt7621: make the reset control optional

The EN751221 I2C controller has no dedicated reset line in its device tree.

Based on Benjamin Larsson's econet-eth-mainline work.
--- a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-mt7621.c
+++ b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-mt7621.c
@@ -82,7 +82,7 @@ static void mtk_i2c_reset(struct mtk_i2c
 {
 	int ret;
 
-	ret = device_reset(i2c->adap.dev.parent);
+	ret = device_reset_optional(i2c->adap.dev.parent);
 	if (ret)
 		dev_err(i2c->dev, "I2C reset failed!\n");
 
